Hai Maybank. Wanted to give a complaint and also a compliment on your staff at Maybank Dataran Bangsar,

 I took the number for Bulk Deposit at 11.30am. and waited til 1.30pm. The number before me is 16people. By the time it was 1.30pm, theres another 4 people til my number to be called. I was waiting then I just feel something was not right. I went and to check on you Chief Cashier room and see no one is there.

So I asked the lady at Counter 8 if the Chief Cashier went to lunch and the lady look surprised and checked. And she said "i think so". As a chief cashier who got a lot of number still, how can she goes to lunch without even telling her subordinates? that just amused me. At least inform the other cashier so that they can cover for me. Its Monday and Selangor is on PH, you should expect the queues. I dont blame her on went to Lunch, but she should at least inform the other people.

The lady at Counter 8 was kind enough to called out the Chief Cashier number. As she checked in the system still lots of us has not been called. Then one lady came from inside and asked her what is she doing (the superior i think) and she told her that the chief cashier has went out and she still got lots of number to be called. And this lady even said "Biarlah number dia. You settled number yang patut you settled"

Mind you. I have been sitting there for 2 damn hours, And that counter 8 lady just keep quiet and keep on calling for the chief cashier number. That lady is Mastura. I can see she's quite new but she had the guts to do whats right and help out YOUR CUSTOMER when the SUPERIOR had the DONT CARE attitude. Kudos to MASTURA at Counter 8 Dataran Maybank on 14 Dec. Thank you soo much. And she even said "Sorry" for me to wait for so long.

Hi Zawani Rohim, please accept our sincere apologies for the service experienced. We will channel your feedback to the respective unit for further investigation. Kindly PM us your full name , IC number, mobile number and description of the staff involved other than Mastura as mentioned earlier. Thank you.

I wanted to lodge a complaint as this is not the 1st time it has encountered.

1. I have a hire-purchase loan under MBB signed in 2011.

2. I have cancelled my standing instruction from Maybank in the same year but yet to be updated.

3. This is the 3rd time this has occurred whereby MBB have deducted my hire-purchase payment from my savings account on 11/12/15, although I have made payment on 08/12/15. If you are going to be deducting from my account like this, might as well I don't make payment at CDM or counter anymore.

4. This is called daylight robbery whereby you are collecting money in both ways. Why is MBB is "the only bank" practicing in this manner. Further, you guys will freeze my savings account without my knowledge and if I ask you guys about notification, you will say that you have sent us letter. Imagine, when I will receive your letter when you send it on Friday and in today's technology we have something called SMS.

5. Come on MBB, I have been a long time customer with you and using your facilities for number of years and yet this is the trust you build with customers. You guys have taken money off my salary which I think is ridiculous and unethical. Today I went MBB to withdraw my salary only to find out that you have taken money from my account which I have made plans with my Family. 

6. Thank you MBB for destroying the day and taking money without any notification or knowledge. You guys can take advantage of signing all 25 pages of documents from us and we have to sign it blindly. When any issues arise, you will say that we have signed clause xx on page xx, as ifi we understand the documentation.

I have notified my company to credit my salary into Maybank because I trust in you and your services..not to misuse my money. How hard is it to ask, "Sir, we have yet to receive your loan payment, can we off-set from your savings account or can you make payment arrangements?".

I will be directing this complaint to BNM as well if there is no proper explanation given as I have the receipt of payment I did before you guys deducted my money. I expect my money to be credited to my savings account immediately.

Rgds
Asger
Savings Acct: 1647 170 11904

Hi Suzanne Lim, the reject code [0089] indicates:

-	Connection issue with either the bank
-	Recipient’s account status. Kindly check with the recipient on the status and you may perform the transaction again. 

You may also try add the account as a favourite interbank transfer and then, try again to perform the transfer or change the mode of transfer to Interbank GIRO transfer. Kindly take note of the charge RM0.11 and the cut off time for the transaction:
